OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1781953372
OL,3,CTwo men sentenced after arson attacks
OL,4,Clinked to prime minister
OL,6,FA car owned by Mr Starmer was set
OL,7,Falight in Kentish Town and was later
OL,8,Ffollowed by two further attacks,
OL,9,Fincluding one rented out to the PM's
OL,10,Fsister-in-law, which he still owned.
OL,12,FLavrynovych and Carpiuc were acting on
OL,13,Fthe orders of an anonymous Telegram
OL,14,Fuser called El Money who was
OL,15,Freportedly linked to a Russian online
OL,16,Fsabotage network.
OL,18,FThe anonymous Russian speaker had
OL,19,Foffered Lavrynovych #3,000 in
OL,20,Fcryptocurrency if the attacks were
OL,21,Ffilmed and got on the news.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
